cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category as it deals with investigating error behaviour in text entry studies. It may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category as it involves the study of text entry methods. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible category as the paper deals with the effectiveness of error correction mechanisms. Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper discusses injection of errors into the typing stream. Finally, Machine Learning (cs.LG) is a possible category as the paper may involve the use of algorithms to inject errors.
